[{"location":"interact.html#Interacting-with-the-Model","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interacting with the Model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"The package provides an intuitive way to interact with the model. Using Interact.jl, we provide two dashboard views of both single region and country models. This is helpful to understand comparative static changes of a single parameter change.","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html#Dashboards","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Dashboards","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"Both region and country have an associated dashboard function which outputs a plot with multiple panels. The dash function for example prints a quick dashboard for a single region:","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"using LandUse   # hide\nusing NNlib, Flux # hide\nLandUse.dash(19)\nLandUse.savefig(\"single-dash.png\")","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"Similarly, the country dashboard for a 3-region country in period 5 can be obtained via","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"LandUse.cdash(3,5)\nLandUse.savefig(\"k3-dash.png\")","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html#Interaction","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interaction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"The main interaction function is","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"LandUse.i0","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html#LandUse.i0","page":"Interactive Views","title":"LandUse.i0","text":"i0()\n\ninteract with the baseline single city version of the model. This basically calls dashboard(M::Vector{Region},p::Param,i::Int) after creating p from a set of user inputs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"and it opens a Blink.jl window like this one:","category":"page"},{"location":"interact.html","page":"Interactive Views","title":"Interactive Views","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html#Single-City-Model","page":"Single Region","title":"Single City Model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"This page describes the how to use the single city model, what we call a Region.","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html#Parameter-and-Region-Setup","page":"Single Region","title":"Parameter and Region Setup","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"The first step is to obtain a Param type, like so:","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"using LandUse\nusing NNlib, Flux\np = LandUse.Param()\np","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"and then we create a Region :","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"m = LandUse.Region(p)\ntypeof(m)","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"Running a model refers to computing the solution to the equation system defined in the jm function via JuMP.jl at all periods:","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"LandUse.jm","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html#LandUse.jm","page":"Single Region","title":"LandUse.jm","text":"solve model at current Param p and starting at point x0\n\nKeyword:\n\nestimateθ: whether the sequence of theta_u should be a choice variable or not. default false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"We compute a starting value x_0, and then supply the period t solution vector as starting value to the period t+1 problem. We obtain this model run via","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"x,M,p = LandUse.run(p)  # solution vectors, Region in each period, Param\nM","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"And you can just index the M vector to look at a certain period in detail:","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"M[4]","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html#Change-Parameter-Values","page":"Single Region","title":"Change Parameter Values","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"The constructor to the Param type accepts a keyword par which has to be dict. You can change the default values by using the appropriate key => value pairs:","category":"page"},{"location":"model.html","page":"Single Region","title":"Single Region","text":"p2 = LandUse.Param(par = Dict(:α => 0.5))\np2.α","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html#Country","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"LandUse.Country","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html#LandUse.Country","page":"Country","title":"LandUse.Country","text":"Country\n\nA Country is a collection of single Region's. There is free migration across regions (same utilty everywhere). What characterises a Region are different θs in their respective urban sectors.\n\nShared Characteristics\n\nIn all regions, the following characteristics are shared:\n\ntotal population\nrural wage\nrural productivity\nrural land price ρ\nrent and food price\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"Similarly to a single region, constructing a Country requires a parameter vector. We have to require at least 2 regions for this work. In this example we create a country with K=3 regions, where the first region has 50% of all available space, and the the rest is split equally between cities 2 and 3 (key :kshare). The key :factors should be ones(K) by default, it allows an exogenous mulitplicative shift of productivity theta_u. Same for :gs which is a growth shift (by default zero). This is useful to experiment with different growth trajectories for regions according to which we would set the theta_u of region ik to:","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"p.θu * p.factors[ik] * exp(p.gs[ik] * (p.it-1))","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"Here we create 3 regions with equal theta_us:","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"using LandUse   # hide\nusing NNlib, Flux # hide\npk = LandUse.Param(par = Dict(:K => 3, \n                              :kshare => [0.5,0.25,0.25],\n                              :factors => ones(3),\n                              :gs => zeros(3)))\nc3 = LandUse.Country(pk)      \nc3","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html#Solving-for-a-Country-in-one-period","page":"Country","title":"Solving for a Country in one period","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"We use the Country type mainly to keep country-wide variables in one place. The actual computation of the equilibrium is again performed in JuMP.jl in the jc function:","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"LandUse.jc","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html#LandUse.jc","page":"Country","title":"LandUse.jc","text":"solve a Country at point x0\n\nkeywords:\n\nestimateθ: whether the sequence of theta_u should be a choice variable\nsolve : solve the model (true) or return the model object for debugging?\nfit_allyears : try to match the population distribution in all available years or just a single year.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"The main difference to the single city solution is that this imposes certain constraints on the chosen theta_u sequence. Please consult the source code of jc for more details.","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html#Running-a-Country","page":"Country","title":"Running a Country","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"As before, we want to compute the country solution at a sequence of dates. This can be done with the runk. The default keywords run a 2-country setup:","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"x,C,p = LandUse.runk()  # sol vector, Country in each t, param\nC","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"and as before, a certain index contains the country in that period:","category":"page"},{"location":"country.html","page":"Country","title":"Country","text":"C[6].R   # regions in period 6","category":"page"},{"location":"reference.html#Function-Reference","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference.html","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Index","text":"Modules = [LandUse]","category":"page"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.CParam","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.CParam","text":"A Country-wide Parameter struct\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Param","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Param","text":"Parameter Struct\n\nThis struct defines the parameter type for the model. It reads default values from the file src/params.json. Those values can be overridden by supplying a Dict to the constructor with key => value pairs:\n\np = LandUse.Param(par = Dict(:η => 0.1))\n\ncreates a Param instance with agglomeration forces set to 0.1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Region","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Region","text":"Region type\n\nUrban expansion model with flexible commuting cost and differential supply elasticity. This represents a single region. A region contains one potential urban area, and a rural area. A Region can be part of a wider Country.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Urban","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Urban","text":"Urban Model\n\nThis model has a fixed price of land ρr in the rural sector. Differently to our baseline model, where ρr is a GE object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference.html#Base.convert-Tuple{LandUse.CParam}","page":"Function Index","title":"Base.convert","text":"convert a country param to one param for each region\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.D-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.D","text":"Population Density at location l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.D2-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Region}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.D2","text":"Population Density at location l. second version, independent of Lu\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.EqSys!-Tuple{Vector{Float64}, LandUse.Country}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.EqSys!","text":"Computes the entries of the residual vector u\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Eqsys!-Tuple{Vector{Float64}, LandUse.Region, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Eqsys!","text":"Eqsys!(F::Vector{Float64},m::Region,p::Param)\n\ncompute system of equations for the general (with flexible ϵ).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Eqsys!-Tuple{Vector{Float64}, LandUse.Urban, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Eqsys!","text":"Eqsys!(F::Vector{Float64},m::Urban,p::Param)\n\ncompute system of equations for the general (with flexible ϵ).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.GDP-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.GDP","text":"GDP\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.H-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.H","text":"housing supply at location l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Rmk-Tuple{LandUse.Country}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Rmk","text":"Country Rural Market Clearing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Rmk-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Rmk","text":"Rural Market Clearing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Srh-Tuple{LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Srh","text":"Residential Land in Rural sector. equation (20)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Yr-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Yr","text":"Production of Rural Good\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.Yu-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.Yu","text":"Production of Urban Good\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cfun-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cfun","text":"cost of construction at location l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.compute_ξw-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.compute_ξw","text":"compute_ξw()\n\nComputes input parameter ξw directly from data. Notice that 1 - xi_w is the  elasticity of speed to wage income. We measure from individual commuting data in ENL (Enquete National de Logement) an increase in commuting speed of about 11% from 1984 to 2013. This function returns \n\nxi_w = 1 - frac11Delta theta_u\n\nwhere Delta theta_u stands for the percentage increase in urban wage from 1984 to 2013.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.copydb-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.copydb","text":"copy dropbox data to in/ folder\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cr-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cr","text":"optimal rural good consumption at location l. Equation (7) divided by p\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cs_plots-Tuple{LandUse.Region, LandUse.Param, Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cs_plots","text":"single spatial cross sections region\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cu-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cu","text":"optimal urban good consumption at location l. Equation (8)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cu_input-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cu_input","text":"Amount of Urban Good (numeraire) required to build housing at l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.cur-Tuple{LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.cur","text":"urban good consumption in rural sector. Equation (8)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.d-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.d","text":"commuting distance\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dash-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dash","text":"dash(it;par = Dict())\n\nHelper function for quick Region dashboard.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dashboard-Tuple{Vector{LandUse.Country}, Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dashboard","text":"dashboard(C::Vector{Country},it::Int)\n\nDashboard for a Country in period it\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dashboard-Tuple{Vector{LandUse.Region}, LandUse.Param, Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dashboard","text":"dashboard(M::Vector{Region},p::Param,i::Int; objvalue = nothing)\n\nModel dashboard for a single Region.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dashk20-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dashk20","text":"dashk20(;save = false)\n\nProduce and optionally save model output for 20 city version.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dataframe-Tuple{Vector{LandUse.Country}}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dataframe","text":"Obtain a Time Series from an array of Country as a DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.dataframe-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{T}, LandUse.Param}} where T<:LandUse.Model","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.dataframe","text":"Obtain a Time Series for a single region as a DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.expmodel-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.expmodel","text":"Estimate exponential model on spatial density. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.expmodel-Tuple{LandUse.Country}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.expmodel","text":"Compute exponential decay model of density for each region in a country\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.firstnorm-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.firstnorm","text":"normalize a vector wrt it's first element\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.foc_Lr-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.foc_Lr","text":"FOC of rural firm wrt labor Lr\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.foc_Sr-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.foc_Sr","text":"FOC of rural firm wrt land Sr\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.getfringe-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.getfringe","text":"Get Fringe from indifference condition\n\nAt the fringe phi we have the condition\n\nw(0) - tau(phi) = w_r\n\nwhich can be rearranged to obtain a map from w(0) - w_r = tau(phi).\n\nThe function takes w(0) - w_r as argument x. then we give tau(phi) \tto its inverse function to get back phi\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.i0-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.i0","text":"i0()\n\ninteract with the baseline single city version of the model. This basically calls dashboard(M::Vector{Region},p::Param,i::Int) after creating p from a set of user inputs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.i0k-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.i0k","text":"i0k()\n\ninteract with the 2 city model.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.integrate!-Tuple{LandUse.Region, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.integrate!","text":"integrate!(m::Region,p::Param)\n\nperform numerical integration using gauss-laguerre. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.integrate!-Tuple{LandUse.Urban, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.integrate!","text":"integrate!(m::Urban,p::Param)\n\ncould be made much faster by filling a matrix col-wise with integration nodes and doing a matmul on it? have to allocate memory though.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.invτ-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.invτ","text":"inverse commuting cost. cost x → location. Notice we don't consider that cost is zero beyond ϕ: we want to find ϕ here to start with.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.iobj-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.iobj","text":"iobj()\n\nSimilar to i0 but prints the value of the objective function into one of the panels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.isfeasible_grid_row-Tuple{Array, NamedTuple}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.isfeasible_grid_row","text":"checks whether a certain row of the grid together with a starting value x0  produces a valid solution in all periods.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue10-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue10","text":"plot phi_k vs L_uk for all regions k and different eps slopes. relates to https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/10\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue11-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue11","text":"measure increase in land value at fringe. by default starts in 1960 and measures increase up to 2020.\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/11\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue15-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue15","text":"https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/15\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue36-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue36","text":"https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/36\n\nsame growth in sectors  i. high cbar vs low sbar: show implied city density time series to see that only that config works  ii. show falling housing spending share as well\nimplications of growth in either sector only\nidentify commuting cost params by matching time series data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue59-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue59","text":"run model with flat epsilon\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/59\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue60-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue60","text":"run model with agglomeration forces\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/60\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue64-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue64","text":"run model with congestion forces\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/64\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue66-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue66","text":"run multi city with congestion\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/66\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue67-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue67","text":"five city cross section\n\nhttps://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/67\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue9-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue9","text":"plot phi_k vs Luk for all regions k. relates to https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/9\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue_21","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue_21","text":"https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/21\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.issue_22-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.issue_22","text":"https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl/issues/22\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.jc-Tuple{LandUse.Country, Vector{T} where T}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.jc","text":"solve a Country at point x0\n\nkeywords:\n\nestimateθ: whether the sequence of theta_u should be a choice variable\nsolve : solve the model (true) or return the model object for debugging?\nfit_allyears : try to match the population distribution in all available years or just a single year.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.jm-Tuple{LandUse.Param, LandUse.Region, NamedTuple}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.jm","text":"solve model at current Param p and starting at point x0\n\nKeyword:\n\nestimateθ: whether the sequence of theta_u should be a choice variable or not. default false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.k20output-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.k20output","text":"Produces output from 20-city model. In particular comparison with single city case, and extension with d1, d2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.k5-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.k5","text":"5 country case\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.latex_param-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.latex_param","text":"print default param to latex table\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.maxnorm-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.maxnorm","text":"normalize a vector wrt it's maximal element\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.multik-Tuple{Dict}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.multik","text":"Runs K regions as a country and produces 2 plots\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.nearstart-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.nearstart","text":"you just had a failed start at p\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.objective-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.objective","text":"objective(x; moments = false, plot = false, save = false, fname = \"moments\")\n\nmoment objective function for an optimizer\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.objective1-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.objective1","text":"objective1(;save = false)\n\nrun objective function at default parameter\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.output_paper-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.output_paper","text":"produces all output from the model needed to compile the paper.\n\nThis uses current baseline parameters defined in params.json\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.p2Flux-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.p2Flux","text":"p2Flux(p::Param)\n\nmap param to Flux Chain to get starting value\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.p2x-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.p2x","text":"p2x(p::Param)\n\nmap param to x for objective function quick eval this is the inverse of x2dict.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.pcy-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.pcy","text":"aggregate per capita income\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.plot_dens_years-Tuple{Vector{LandUse.Region}, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.plot_dens_years","text":"plot densities for all years\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.plotk20-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.plotk20","text":"plotk20(;save = false)\n\nProduce model output for 20 city version.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.poparea_data-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.poparea_data","text":"load population and area data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.popdata_mapyears-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.popdata_mapyears","text":"find closest year in population data to model years\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.prepare_data-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.prepare_data","text":"prepare_data(p::Param; digits = 9)\n\nTakes raw csv data and prepares to be used in model. writes to csv input files.\n\nSmoothing of Productivity Series\n\nWe take the following steps to obtain a smoothed series for theta_r and theta_u:\n\nWe obtain the estimated series at annual frequency.\nWe subset both series to start in 1840 and end in 2015 (rural productivity ends in that year)\nWe linearly interpolate the missing interwar years.\nSmoothing is done via the [smooth] function from the QuantEcon package: we use the default Hann window and a 15-year window size. We experimented with the window size until high-frequency oscillations disappear.\nOur rural productivity series gets very volatile from 2000 onwards, and in fact one would find a decreasing rural productivity series if we applied our smoother to post 2000 data. Therefore from the year 2000 onwards, we grow the smoothed series forward with 1% annual growth. Given that 2000 is very close to the final new steady state of the model, the actual choice of growth rate has only a small impact on our results.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.q-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.q","text":"house price function at l. equation (12)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.qr-Tuple{LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.qr","text":"rural house price from land price\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.rel_cityarea-Tuple{LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.rel_cityarea","text":"rel_cityarea(m::Model)\n\nComputes city area relative to total rural land use. This is the model moment related to the data moment artificialized land relative to agricultural land in 2015. We measure this to be 18.3% in the data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.relpop-Tuple{Vector{LandUse.Country}}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.relpop","text":"return model relative population in each year to largest city largest city is city 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.run-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.run","text":"run Single region model for all time periods\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.run-Tuple{NamedTuple, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.run","text":"run Single region model for all time periods\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.runestim-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.runestim","text":"runestim(;steps = 1000,fname = \"moments\")\n\nRun the default differential evolution optimizer from BlackBoxOptim.jl\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.runk-Tuple{}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.runk","text":"run Multi-region model for all time periods starting from  the single city starting value. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.startvals_impl-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.startvals_impl","text":"collect valid starting values for the k country case by reusing the first period solution \tof each preceding step in θu along the sequence\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.startvals_k-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.startvals_k","text":"startvals_k()\n\nFind feasible starting values for multi city case (2 to 5 cities) and write to disk. By default return the saved dict with start param and initial guess vector x0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.startvals_par-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.startvals_par","text":"helper function to prepare country param\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.targets-Tuple{LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.targets","text":"returns a dict of empirical targets for the model\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.ts_plots-Tuple{Any, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.ts_plots","text":"ts_plots(M,p::Param;fixy = false)\n\nTime series plots for a single Region M.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.update!-Tuple{LandUse.Country, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.update!","text":"update!(c::Country,p::Vector{Param},x::Vector{Float64})\n\nUpdate a Country object with a current vector of choice variables x supplied by the solver. The ordering in x is:\n\nb: ratio of labor to land in region 1\nr: land rent\npr: relative price rural good\n4 : (K+3), Sr: amount of land use in rural production (complement of Srh)\n(K+4) : (2K+3), Lu: urban pop in each k\n(2K+4) : end, θu: urban prod in each k\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.update!-Tuple{LandUse.Region, LandUse.Param, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.update!","text":"update!(m::Region,p::Param,x::Vector{Float64})\n\nupdate a single Region with a Param at choices x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.update!-Tuple{LandUse.Urban, LandUse.Param, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.update!","text":"update!(m::Urban,p::Param,x::Vector{Float64})\n\nupdate a single region a parameter vector at choices x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.utility-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.utility","text":"Utility function equation (5)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.w-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.w","text":"wage at location l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.wr-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.wr","text":"rural wage from indifference condition at ϕ. Eq (11)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.wu-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.wu","text":"urban wage at location l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.wu0-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.wu0","text":"urban wage at center\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.x2dict-Tuple{Any}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.x2dict","text":"x2dict(x)\n\nmap vector x to dict for Param\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.xsr-Tuple{LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.xsr","text":"excess subsistence rural worker\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.xsu-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.xsu","text":"excess subsistence urban worker\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.y-Tuple{LandUse.Model, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.y","text":"disposable income: GDP net of commuting costs\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.ρ-Tuple{Float64, LandUse.Param, LandUse.Model}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.ρ","text":"land price function at l. equation (15)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.τ-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param, Float64}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.τ","text":"commuting cost: location x → cost\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.χ-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.χ","text":"housing supply shifter at l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference.html#LandUse.ϵ-Tuple{Float64, Float64, LandUse.Param}","page":"Function Index","title":"LandUse.ϵ","text":"housing supply elasticity at l\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#LandUse.jl-documentation","page":"Home","title":"LandUse.jl documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Build Status)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Intro","page":"Home","title":"Intro","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This is the documentation for julia computation code used in the paper Structural Change, Land Use and Urban Expansion (link) by Coeurdacier, Oswald and Teignier. The package repository is available on github at https://github.com/floswald/LandUse.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"There is an associated R package LandUseR whose website, documents for the data measurement parts used in the paper, basically the code for sections B.6 and B.7 of our online appendix (link)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\"index.md\", \"model.md\", \"country.md\", \"interact.md\", \"reference.md\"]\nDepth = 1","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Version-and-timestamp","page":"Home","title":"Version and timestamp","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"VERSION\nusing Dates; now()","category":"page"}]
